A busy roundabout in Berkshire is set to be closed overnight for roadworks.The A308 Braywick Roundabout, between Windsor and Maidenhead, will be shut from 21:00 BST until 06:00 on Wednesday for resurfacing work.Diversions will be in place during the closure to manage both motorway and non-motorway traffic that would normally access to and from the A308(M) spur.Royal Borough of Windsor and Maidenhead  councillor Geoff Hill, cabinet member for highways and transport, said the work had been "timed to minimise impact on road users."
The council has asked motorists to follow its suggested diversion routes. 
